---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Contraflow Riding on One-Way Streets"
  year="2023"
  category="Urban Mobility · Safety Analysis"
  tools={['Python', 'GeoPandas', 'Shapely', 'QGIS', 'OpenStreetMap', 'Populus']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Tel Aviv's Florentine neighborhood is a dense grid of narrow one-way streets — typical of older
        urban fabric built before the car. As shared e-scooters spread through the city, enforcement
        reports pointed to riders frequently traveling against traffic direction, raising safety concerns
        for riders and pedestrians alike. This analysis set out to measure exactly how much contraflow
        riding was happening, where, and by whom.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Map — Florentine Contraflow Analysis</h2>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/contraflow.png`}
      alt="Map showing contraflow e-scooter trips in the Florentine neighborhood, Tel Aviv"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      Shared e-scooter trip segments classified as contraflow (against one-way direction) in the
      Florentine neighborhood, overlaid on the street network.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Pulled raw GPS trip data from the <strong>Populus</strong> mobility platform and street geometry with directional attributes from <strong>OpenStreetMap</strong>.</li>
      <li>Used <strong>GeoPandas</strong> and <strong>Shapely</strong> to map-match each trip trajectory to its street segment and compare travel bearing against the segment's permitted direction.</li>
      <li>Flagged a trip as contraflow when its bearing deviated beyond a defined angular threshold — filtering out GPS noise — then aggregated results by street, time of day and operator.</li>
      <li>Produced final cartography and classification in <strong>QGIS</strong>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Contraflow riding concentrated heavily on a handful of corridors — giving enforcement teams a
        precise, prioritized target list instead of a citywide guess. Cross-referencing those corridors
        with the city's cycling infrastructure plans also surfaced strong candidates for new contraflow
        bike lanes, turning a safety problem into an infrastructure opportunity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
